This file has two goals. First, it contains the file that generates the bixi example for the package. This is not part
of the manuscript.

The second goal is generating the results and the data from the bixi example.
The files are:

1. 1_generate_train_test_splits.R it generates all the train/test splits (for 50 replications and different
missing proportions) and saves them inside ./data/Bixi/
source it to run it.

2. 2_fit_bktr.R. fits BKTR model to all splits and saves fit files to disk. Slow. 
Takes around 25 minutes per fit and we have 100 fits. Also source it. each fit is saved inside
./data/Bixi. source it to run it.

3. 3_fit_IMR.R  same with but with our method. fits are also saved to disk. source it.

4. 4_generate_results_table.R this file generates (prints) the table reported in the article using the
saved fit files. Also source it.

helper contains helper functions. ignore it as it's laoded by the other files.
